{"title_page": "Vidhi (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Vidhi\n| image                    =Vidhi Sun TV Serial.jpg\n| caption                  = \n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|ta|\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf}}\n| genre                    = [[Tamil television soap opera|soap opera]] <br> [[Family]] <br> [[Romance film|Romance]]  <br> [[Drama]] <br> [[Medical]]\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| writer                   = Thavan Suppaiya <br> Marudhu Shankar (Dialogues)\n| director                 = K.Shiva (1-101).   <br> G.Stalin (102-262\n| creative_director        = A.Guru Baran\n| starring                 = Sreeja <br> Rashmi Jayraj <br> Jegathish <br> Ravi Raj <br> Anu <br> Yuvasri <br> Surjith Ansary <br> Lenin Anpan\n| theme_music_composer     = [[Dhina]]\n| opentheme                = \"Vidhiye Vidhiye\" <br> [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]] <br> Rita (Vocals) <br> [[Vairamuthu]] (Lyrics)\n| country                  = [[India]]\n| language                 = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 301\n| list_episodes            = \n| producer                 = [[San Media Ltd]]\n| location                 = [[Tamil Nadu]]\n| cinematography           = S.Ezhilselvan\n| editor                   = C.S.Rajapradeep<br> Muralikrishnan\n| camera                   = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = approx. 20-22 minutes per episode\n| company                  = San Media Limited\n| first_aired              = {{start date|df=yes|2017|3|6}}\n| last_aired               = {{end date|df=yes|2018|1|20}}\n| preceded_by              = Nijangal\n| followed_by              = Priyamanaval (R)\n| related                  = \n| screenplay               = C.U.Muthuselvan\n| story                    = Lidya Paul\n| channel                  = [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]]\n}}\n\n'''''Vidhi''''' ({{lang-ta|\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf}}) is a 2017-2018 Indian-[[Tamil Language]] [[Tamil television soap opera |family soap opera]] starring Sreeja,  Rashmi Jayraj, Jegathish, Ravi Raj, Surjith Ansary and Anu.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/tamil/sun-tv-airs-a-new-serial-titled-vidhi/articleshow/57513241.cms|title=Sun TV airs a new serial titled Vidhi|date=7 March 2017|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=31 May 2018}}</ref> It replaced [[Nijangal (TV series)|Nijangal]] and was broadcast on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] on Monday to Saturday from 6 March 2017 to 20 January 2018 at 1:00PM ([[Indian Standard Time|IST]]) for 301 Episodes. It was produced by [[San Media Ltd]] and directed by Stalin Iniya. The title track was composed by [[Dhina]] and sung by [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]] and Rita with lyrics by [[Vairamuthu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sunnetwork.in/program-details.aspx?IProgramID=C/uyiKbxunE=%20&ShowType=banner|title=Vidhi Serial Page|work=|publisher=www.sunnetwork.in}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamil.filmibeat.com/television/sun-tv-telecast-3-new-serials-prime-time-045055.html|title=\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb7\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bcd.. \u0bae\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbf, \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bbf, \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf... \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd!|work=|publisher=tamil.filmibeat.com}}</ref> It ended on 20 January 2018.\n\n==Synopsis==\nDr.Nila(Sreeja), a pious young lady, works at the government hospital and is praised by her seniors for her work. She falls in love with Raghu (Jegathish), but the relationship strains under pressure from society.\n\n===Original Plot===\nNila (Sreeja) and Raghu (Jegathish) a married couple, who adopt a child, born to an unmarried woman, Dhiya. Problems arise in the family when Raghu's sister, Chitra marries Siddarth, the biological father of Nila's adopted child.\n\n==Cast==\n===Main cast===\n{{div col}}\n* Sreeja as Dr.Nila Raghu\n* Rashmi Jayraj as Dhiya Dev\n* R. Vibhu (Jagadeesh) as Raghu\n* Karan Sagar as Dev\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Additional cast===\n{{div col}}\n* Parthi as Magesh\n* Ravi Raj\n* Bombay Babu as Azhagesan\n* Revathy Shankar as Maragadham\n* Surjith Ansary as Dhinesh\n* Anu as Chithira\n* Yuvasri\n* Sarath Chandra\n* Mounica Devi\n* Anitha\n* Hemalatha\n* Lenin Anpan\n* Devipriya as Punithavathi\n* Haripriya as Mythili\n* Sripriya\n* Shayrin\n* David\n* Surender\n* Rajesh\n* Vairavaraj\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Title song==\nThe title suntv\nsong was written by lyricist [[Vairamuthu]], composed by [[Dhina]] and sung by [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]] and Rita.\n\n===Soundtrack===\n{{tracklist\n| headline       = Track list\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| title1         = Vidhiye Vidhiye <br> (\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc7 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc7) Title Song\n| lyrics1        = [[Vairamuthu]]\n| extra1         = [[Karthik rita\n(singer)|Karthik]] and Rita\n| music1         = [[Dhina]] \n| length1        = 3:00\n}}\n\n==Production==\nThe series was directed by Stalin Iniya. It was produced by [[San Media Ltd]], along with the production crew of 2004-2017 [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] serials [[Ahalya (TV series)|Ahalya]] (2004-2006), Bandham (2006-2009), [[Uravugal]] (2009-2012) and [[Bommalattam (TV series)|Bommalattam]] (2012-2016).\n\n==International broadcast==\nThe Series was released on 6 March 2017 on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] alongside [[Mahalakshmi (TV series)|Mahalakshmi]] and [[Sumangali (TV series)|Sumangali]], the series also airs on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV HD]]. The series was also broadcast internationally on Channel's international distribution. \n* It aired in [[Sri Lanka]], [[South East Asia]], [[Middle East]], [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Europe]], [[Oceania]], [[South Africa]] and [[Sub Saharan Africa]] on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]].\n* The drama has episodes on the app [[Sun Nxt]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thetechportal.com/2017/06/16/sun-tv-debuts-digital-content-streaming-platform-sun-nxt/|title=With Sun NXT, Sun TV Network steps foot in the burgeoning digital streaming space of India|work=|publisher=thetechportal.com|access-date=10 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111045112/https://thetechportal.com/2017/06/16/sun-tv-debuts-digital-content-streaming-platform-sun-nxt/|archive-date=11 November 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* It is also available via the internet protocol television service, [[Lebara|Lebara Play]] and [[YuppTV]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20141007220928/http://www.suntvnetwork.in/tv-channel-details.aspx?Channelid=1&channelname=SUN%20TV&LanguageID=1&Type=q Official Website] {{in lang|en}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/suntv Sun TV on YouTube]\n* [http://www.suntv.in/ Sun TV Network] {{in lang|en}}\n* [http://www.sun.in Sun Group] {{in lang|en}}\n\n\n\n\n{{Sun TV shows}}\n[[Category:Sun TV television series]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language television series]]\n[[Category:2017 Tamil-language television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2018 Tamil-language television series endings]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Vidhi\n| image                    =Vidhi Sun TV Serial.jpg\n| caption                  = \n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|ta|\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf}}\n| genre                    = [[Tamil television soap opera|soap opera]] <br> [[Family]] <br> [[Romance fil